The Kaduna State chapter of Military, Police and Paramilitary Public Relations Officers weekend held a 15-kilometre route march to promote synergy. The route march, held at Murtala Square and Ahmadu Bello Stadium in Kaduna metropolis witnessed a long row of joint security agencies chanting solidarity songs. Police Public Relations Officer Mukhtar Aliyu said the match was aimed at dispelling the wrong impression of lack of synergy among agencies. He said: “Inter-agency synergy is believed by members of all agencies to be a catalyst for cohesion which can result in peaceful co-existence for development to thrive. This is the first time we are organizing something of such, and there is going to be subsequent programmes and the programs is to ensure and synergyies and collaborate among all security services.”